<br>
Group composition:<br>
<br>
50+ chanter<br>
50+ Shaman (JBB &amp; dog are highly recomended)<br>
50+ necro<br>
49+ wizard<br>
<br>
Technique is pretty simple:  fear kite him.  Have a druid/wizard pull him with snare (Atol's Spectral Shackles works fine for wizard.)  From there, have either the chanter or necro fear him.  It is better for the chanter to fear him so the necro can load all of their dots as physically possible.  Shaman should also do the same, especially now that dots can stack.  All pets should be attacking him as soon as possible, once he is feared.  Slow lands fairly easily, as does the Malo line of spells.  If the shaman has a JBB, keep clicking it as much as possible.  Epic is a nice touch.  Same with druid and necro epic (if you have a druid or necro with epic.)  More dots = better kill.  Once the HPs are moving down consistantly, the Wizard can start chain casting Ice Comet.  Staff of Temperate Flux can be *somewhat* handy for the lowered cold resistance against him.  If the wizard has a large enough mana pool, he should be dead by the time he/she runs out of mana.  And bam, you have a shiny new spoon!<br>
<br>
Best case for this is mostly 55+ characters, expecially wizard.  As playing a 56 wizard and 55 shaman at the same time for a Cazel kill, Ice Comet usually hit for full, except a few times.<br>
<br>
Any questions?<br>
